								<div class="title" id="post-title-4231912">
																		Author Post -- All Skippers Are Bastards, But Some are /Bastards/
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252526" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1556427686 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Apr 2019 05:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4231912">
									

<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Well I been drinkin' again<br />
And I know it's a sin<br />
But I just can't refuse an old friend<br />
Cause life is gettin' me down<br />
And I been two times around<br />
And there ain't nothing but pain around the bend<br />
I'm not made for the time<br />
I'm born in the wrong century<br />
There's too much craziness here<br />
In twenty-five years I have used all the tears in my eyes</em></p>
<p><span style="margin-left: 50%">Kansas &#8212; &quot;<a href="https://youtu.be/p6yt6yYmx7g">Two Cents Worth</a>&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Part 8 is here, and only a little bit delayed. This one is a doozy. I'd ask that you keep any spoilery comments hidden inside collapsibles.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary&nbsp;(w/&nbsp;Spoilers!)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Close</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>SURPRISE, WESTBROOK WAS A BASTARD THE ENTIRE TIME!</p>
<p>So yeah, this obviously sheds a new light on everything that's happened in the previous seven tales, and should make many seemingly innocuous moments much more Sinister in hindsight. Allow me to catalogue some of them:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>&quot;Wasn't sure if you'd still remember.&quot; He paused, as if considering that statement</strong>, then added, &quot;Hypoxia tends to leave people a little loopy.&quot;<br />
<span style="margin-left: 50%">&#8212; &quot;An Unexpected Interview&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>[Literally any of the scenes where he's giving Florence a pep talk.]<br />
<span style="margin-left: 50%">&#8212; &quot;Individual Efficacy&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>&quot;Maybe we should talk about some of your secrets instead.&quot;</strong></p>
<p><strong>She felt him tense up</strong> at the touch of her nails on his skin. &quot;Oh?&quot;<br />
<span style="margin-left: 50%">&#8212; &quot;Finding A Scalpel&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>I am aware of your fondness for Agent Elsinger, so I will remind you that the Nightingale Contingency exists for her own protection. You know her better than anyone, so you know how tenuous her allegiance is. The Contingency ensures her loyalty, and her loyalty guarantees her life. More than that, it has made her happy. If you truly care about her, you will not rob her of that.</p>
<p>I find it just as distasteful as you do, but it is a necessary evil — <strong>as you yourself assured me when the Contingency was first implemented.</strong><br />
<span style="margin-left: 50%">&#8212; &quot;The Greater Good, and Other Necessary Evils&quot;</span></p>
</blockquote>
<p>There's more, obviously &#8212; like the intentional misalignment of the date in the location card and in Westbrook's dialogue in &quot;An Unexpected Interview&quot;, but I'll let you find them yourselves. Suffice to say that I tried to drop enough hints to make this predictable without making it obvious.</p>
<p>Also, in case it isn't clear, Westbrook is a Bad Person. If you feel bad for him, that's fine &#8212; he is meant to be somewhat sympathetic, after all &#8212; but he is not a good guy. He did an extremely bad thing, and the fact that he feels bad about it now does nothing to change what he did or who he hurt. Some things cannot be forgiven or fixed. This is one of them.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Crit credits go out to:</p>
<ul>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ch00bakka" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1238719); return false;">ch00bakka</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/get-out-of-her-way">Get Out Of Her Way</a></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span> &#8212; <a href="/a-confluence-of-clandestine-conferences">A Confluence of Clandestine Conferences</a></li>
<li><span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tawny0" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2244665); return false;">tawny0</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p>Part 9 is <em>meant</em> to come out on Tuesday, but might be a bit delayed by the fact that I have finals next week.</p>

							</div>

								
					
